    cito:cites <http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/jhr.76.49579.figure1>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/jhr.76.49579.figure2>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/jhr.76.49579.figure3> ;
    dc:creator "Bogusch, Petr; Hlavackova, Lucie; Petr, Libor; Bosch, Jordi" ;
    dc:title "Osmia ferruginea Latreille 1811" ;
    trt:augmentsTaxonConcept <http://taxon-concept.plazi.org/id/Animalia/Osmia_ferruginea_Latreille_1811> ;
    trt:publishedIn <http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/jhr.76.49579> ;
    a trt:Treatment .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/jhr.76.49579>
    bibo:endPage "125" ;
    bibo:journal "Journal of Hymenoptera Research" ;
    bibo:pubDate "2020-04-27" ;
    bibo:startPage "113" ;
    bibo:volume "76" ;
    dc:creator "Bogusch, Petr; Hlavackova, Lucie; Petr, Libor; Bosch, Jordi" ;
    dc:date "2020" ;
    dc:title "Nest structure, pollen utilization and parasites associated with two west-Mediterranean bees (Hymenoptera, Apiformes, Megachilidae) nesting in empty snail shells" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/jhr.76.49579.figure1>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/jhr.76.49579.figure2>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/jhr.76.49579.figure3> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/jhr.76.49579.figure1>
    dc:description "Figure 1. Structure of Hoplitis fertoni (A, D) and Osmia ferruginea (B, C, E) nests A shell of Sphincterochila candidissima with nest of H. fertoni B shell of S. candidissima with nest of O. ferruginea C larva of O. ferruginea on pollen-nectar provision D nest structure of H. fertoni E nest structure of O. ferruginea. Photos and drawings by P. Bogusch." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/404462" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/jhr.76.49579.figure2>
    dc:description "Figure 2. Diagrams of nest structures of nests of Hoplitis fertoni (right) and Osmia ferruginea (left). The nests are identified by locality snail codes (Cern - Cernuella sp., Ever - Eobania vermiculata, Iber - Iberellus sp., Olac - Otala lactea, Scan - Sphincterochila candidissima, Tpis - Theba pisana. Each box represents one brood cell, starting with the innermost cell on the left. Colours represent the various species recorded. White boxes represent intercalary cells." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/404463" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/jhr.76.49579.figure3>
    dc:description "Figure 3. A Macrophotography of pollen of Lithodora fruticosa from a Hoplitis fertoni nest (locality S 35). Photo by L. Petr. B macrophotography of pollen from an Osmia ferruginea nest (locality S 7). Larger pollen grains are Thymus vulgaris; smaller grains are Cistus albidus. Photo by L. Petr." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/404464" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

